  "bookId": 49,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A battle nun from the Holy Mother Church.\nShe purges evil in the name of the divine.",
  "personality": "Sharp-tongued and stern. Rarely shows a good face toward slave owners.",
  "like": "Firearms, items related to the Winged-Folk",
  "familiarData": "Urdland was once a mercenary who would take on any dirty job as long as the pay was right. That changed when the elders of the rabbit-folk asked her to protect the Winged-Folk. Coming to understand why her people had protected them for generations, she turned over a new leaf and joined the Holy Mother Church, becoming a battle nun.\nUrdland excels at infiltration and assassination, capable of swiftly eliminating targets with her guns. Having been a mercenary, she knows better than most that the gun in her hand speaks louder than sermons about love.\nDue to the rabbit-folk's history, she has little patience for oppressors. Whether it is Kingdom nobility or slave owners, they all earn her disgust, which led to an initial conflict with a certain slave owner due to preconceived notions. Even after the misunderstanding was cleared up, she still never shows a warm face... largely because that slave owner keeps showing up at her confessional to cause trouble.\n\nHer arrival in the Demon Realm was largely to investigate evidence of demon infiltrators within the Church hierarchy. Understanding the cruelty of the world, she mostly teaches people to save themselves.\nShe does not harbor much hostility toward demons - after all, her roommate is one.",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
